_⚠️ Potential issue_

**Potential infinite update loop with container size changes**

The reactive statement updates the stamp when container size changes, which triggers an 'update' event, potentially causing an infinite loop if the parent also reacts to updates by changing container size.



```diff
 	// Scale stamps when canvas size changes
 	$: if (containerWidth > 0 && containerHeight > 0) {
 		const pos = getAbsolutePosition(stamp);
-		if (pos.x !== stamp.x || pos.y !== stamp.y || pos.size !== stamp.size) {
+		// Use tolerance to avoid floating point comparison issues
+		const tolerance = 0.01;
+		const hasChanged = 
+			Math.abs(pos.x - stamp.x) > tolerance || 
+			Math.abs(pos.y - stamp.y) > tolerance || 
+			Math.abs(pos.size - stamp.size) > tolerance;
+		
+		if (hasChanged) {
 			const updatedStamp: StampAnnotation = {
 				...stamp,
 				x: pos.x,
 				y: pos.y,
 				size: pos.size
 			};
-			dispatch('update', updatedStamp);
+			// Use requestAnimationFrame to batch updates
+			requestAnimationFrame(() => {
+				dispatch('update', updatedStamp);
+			});
 		}
 	}
```

<!-- suggestion_start -->

<details>
<summary>📝 Committable suggestion</summary>

> ‼️ **IMPORTANT**
> Carefully review the code before committing. Ensure that it accurately replaces the highlighted code, contains no missing lines, and has no issues with indentation. Thoroughly test & benchmark the code to ensure it meets the requirements.

```suggestion
// Scale stamps when canvas size changes
$: if (containerWidth > 0 && containerHeight > 0) {
    const pos = getAbsolutePosition(stamp);
    // Use tolerance to avoid floating point comparison issues
    const tolerance = 0.01;
    const hasChanged =
        Math.abs(pos.x - stamp.x) > tolerance ||
        Math.abs(pos.y - stamp.y) > tolerance ||
        Math.abs(pos.size - stamp.size) > tolerance;

    if (hasChanged) {
        const updatedStamp: StampAnnotation = {
            ...stamp,
            x: pos.x,
            y: pos.y,
            size: pos.size
        };
        // Use requestAnimationFrame to batch updates
        requestAnimationFrame(() => {
            dispatch('update', updatedStamp);
        });
    }
}
```

</details>

<!-- suggestion_end -->

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
In src/lib/components/StampAnnotation.svelte around lines 168 to 179, the
reactive block dispatches an 'update' whenever computed absolute position
differs, which can trigger a parent resize and cause an infinite update loop;
fix by introducing a local sentinel (e.g., lastDispatched = {x,y,size}) and
compare the new computed pos against both the incoming stamp and lastDispatched,
and only call dispatch('update', ...) when the values truly changed relative to
lastDispatched, then update lastDispatched after dispatching so container-driven
re-renders won't re-trigger another dispatch.
```

</details>

