_🛠️ Refactor suggestion_

**Potential issue with backward compatibility fallback**

The fallback to `(stamp as any).stamp` uses an unsafe type assertion. Consider adding proper type checking or migration logic.



```diff
-	$: stampDefinition = stamp.stampId ? getStampById(stamp.stampId) : null;
-	$: stampSvg = stampDefinition?.svg || (stamp as any).stamp || '';
+	// Handle backward compatibility with proper type checking
+	$: stampDefinition = stamp.stampId ? getStampById(stamp.stampId) : null;
+	$: stampSvg = (() => {
+		if (stampDefinition?.svg) return stampDefinition.svg;
+		// Check for legacy stamp property safely
+		const legacyStamp = stamp as any;
+		if (typeof legacyStamp.stamp === 'string') {
+			console.warn('Using legacy stamp format, consider migrating to stampId');
+			return legacyStamp.stamp;
+		}
+		return '';
+	})();
```

